Operatives of the Nigeria Police force have rescued Gift Abikor, a 17 years old student of Federal Government College Rubochi, a village in Kuje area council of the FCT. Confirming the rescue, the spokesperson of the FCT police command, DSP Anjuguri Manzah said the student was rescued unhurt at about 8:30pm on the 31st of January, 2020. Recall that the commissioner of Police FCT, CP Bala Ciroma had ordered a discreet investigation into the abduction of Abiikor, from the residence of one Ahmed Adamu by some unknown armed men in the early hours of Tuesday 28th January, 2020. The unfortunate incident happened at the residence of Ahmed Adamu, which is outside the premises of Federal Government College Rubochi. The police noted that “according to Ahmed Adamu, who reported the incident to them, some armed men stormed his house at about 1am and abducted one Gift Abiikor who was sleeping on the same bed with his (Ahmed Adamu) children.” The Command had also reassured members of the public that it is making concerted effort to rescue the victim and unravel the circumstances behind his abduction. Manzah noted that while reassuring FCT residents of its commitment to protecting lives and property in the Federal Capital Territory, the Command wishes to appreciate FCT residents for supporting it with information and in case of distress, the Command can be reached on any of these hotlines: 08032003913, 08061581938, 07057337653 and 08028940883.